Reverse Malicious APK to Extract C2 Address
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Decompile Android APK files using JADX
Extract and analyze strings from DEX files
Identify Command and Control (C2) server addresses in malicious code
Decode obfuscated strings using common techniques
Create automated analysis scripts for APK investigation
Document findings in a professional security report
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Android application structure
Familiarity with Java programming
Linux command-line proficiency
Basic Python scripting knowledge
Understanding of network protocols
Lab Environment
Al Nafi Cloud Machine: Click Start Lab to access your pre-configured Ubuntu 20.04 environment with:

